The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Bajaj Allianz Life Insurance has launched Bajaj Aliianz Capital Shield  an insurance product aimed at investors with low-risk tolerance and provides a guaranteed maturity value. Providing safety to our investors is very important, Bajaj Allianz CEO Kamesh Goyal said. Capital Shield offers five-time life cover and provides the advantage of double tax benefits under Section 80C and 10(10)D, he said.                            
	 Cognizant Technology Solutions has reported a 31 per cent increase in revenue for the quarter ended September 30 at $734.7 million compared with $558.8 million in the year-ago period.                   
	 Visa Steel is setting up a stainless steel plant at the Kalinganagar industrial complex in Orissa. The company has posted an 115 per cent rise in revenue at Rs 331.14 crore in the second quarter of 2008-09.                             
	 Assam Company Ltd has registered a 92 per cent increase in profit after tax at Rs 24.65 crore for the third quarter ended September 30, 2008, against Rs 12.84 crore in the year-ago period.                             
	 Pegasystems has opened a research and development facility in Hyderabad . The unit will provide Pegasystems with a global research, development, and training footprint.                            
	 Reliance Communications (R-Com) subscribers buying a CDMA lifetime connection worth Rs 299 and a Rs 52 recharge coupon will get free talktime of 1,200 minutes for calling local Reliance numbers and an additional talktime worth Rs 50 for making calls to other numbers.                             
	 Virgin Mobile has launched vKewl priced at Rs. 3,499. The handset offers features such as video recording, 1.3 mega pixel camera, MP3 player, FM radio and MMS.                             
	 Spaces Home amp; Beyond has unveiled the Autumn Winter Collection for 2008 called Calico, Caliphas House and Taj Empress.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
